[{"id":"VR876689","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of a double slit experiment, consisting of a vertical barrier with two slits of separation s, and a vertical screen to the right of it. To the left of the barrier, vertical lines indicate monochromatic light, which has wavelength lambda, the separation between the vertical lines. A front view of the screen to the right shows evenly-spaced spots of light. A dashed line is indicated between the center of the slits on the barrier, and the center of the central spot of light on the screen directly to the right of it. Another dashed line which slants upward and to the right is indicated between the center of the slits on the barrier, and the center of the spot of light directly above the central spot of light on the screen. The angle between these two dashed lines is theta. A note states that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR876689.g01.svg\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Monochromatic light of wavelength <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lambda\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"lambda\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>λ</mi></math></span></span> is incident upon two parallel, narrow slits that are a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"s\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>s</mi></math></span></span> apart, as shown in the figure. A screen is located a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"D\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>D</mi></math></span></span> from the slits, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D is much greater than s\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"D is much greater than s\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>D</mi><mo>≫</mo><mi>s</mi></math></span></span>, and an interference pattern forms on the screen as indicated. The angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"theta\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>θ</mi></math></span></span> in the figure is the angle between one leg and the hypotenuse of the right triangle shown. A leg and the hypotenuse of the triangle connect the midpoint of the two slits to the centers of the central bright maximum and the adjacent bright maximum in the interference pattern. If <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"theta\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>θ</mi></math></span></span> is small, what is an approximate expression for <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"theta\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>θ</mi></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR876689_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction s over D\"><math alttext=\"the fraction s over D\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>s</mi><mi>D</mi></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction D over s\"><math alttext=\"the fraction D over s\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>D</mi><mi>s</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction lambda over D\"><math alttext=\"the fraction lambda over D\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>λ</mi><mi>D</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction lambda over s\"><math alttext=\"the fraction lambda over s\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>λ</mi><mi>s</mi></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":3}]